<!-- Using Nexus Magic Hat -->
<event name="LIGHTSPEED_SECTOR_WARP_RADIKAL_HAT">
	<text>You are about to reroute. Below is the Atlas entry for this sector.
	Name: RadiKal Sector
	Type: Neutral
	Dominant Faction: RK Bam, RK Punk, RK Scorch
	Rebel Threat Level: Very Low
	Locations of Interest: RK Labs, Scorch BIL, Pirate Trinity, Hideout
	
	The [style[color:ff3377]]dangerous[[/style]] sector where RadiKal subfactions develop illegal equipment. Rumors say eldritch forces might be involved. Still, specialists from everywhere secretly come to keep up with the tech, attempt to regulate its trade, or steal it.
	Mind whatever Radikal (RK) equipment you have in there!
	[Feedback? @Dj0z on discord.]</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue with the jump.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You prepare to jump to the new co-ordinates, and change your flight path accordingly.</text>
			<variable name="coords_radikal" op="set" val="0"/>
			<variable name="visited_radikal_sector" op="set" val="1"/>

			<variable name="magical_hat_active" op="set" val="0"/>		<!-- this is the only difference. -->
			
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="JUMP_TO_RADIKAL"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Nevermind.</text>
		<event>
			<loadEvent>ATLAS_MENU_NOEQUIPMENT</loadEvent>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<!-- REFS: Darkest Desire v4.1.4 for MV v5.5.1 - NOTE: theses are both secretly ..._HAT REROUTES!!!
<event name="LIGHTSPEED_SECTOR_WARP_DDSOULPLAGUE">
	<text>Name: Nebulous Dead Zone
	Type: Uncolonized
	Unique: True
	Dominant Faction: None
	Rebel Threat Level: Medium (Auto)
	
	Aside from a brief history of Shell occupation prior to its abandonment, this sector remains entirely uncolonized by the galaxy at large. Notable, though, is that this unoccupation is not from a lack of trying. Several factions, and many more minor parties, have attempted to enter this nebulous mass; yet no reports back have ever officially been documented. Rumors point to many things: Slug pirates hunting within the clouds, secret Shell experiments gone wrong, even talk of illegal Duskbringer activity... but nobody has ever returned to say for certain. Thus has this mysterious sector earned its name: the Nebulous Dead Zone. You should stay vigilant, lest you become its next victim.</text>
